<collectingCountry id="45DD19D4FFF4AF56A6846224FF6DFEF9" box="[692,794,266,292]" name="Thailand" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, where the species was first collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="75D00ACFFFF4AF56A48D6200FD08F97D" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="3D755944FFF4AF56A48D6200FD85FE95" blockId="7.[136,1452,266,1696]" box="[189,498,302,328]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A48D6200FD43FE95" bold="true" box="[189,308,302,328]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">
<typeStatus id="E271E7E6FFF4AF56A48D6200FD59FE95" box="[189,302,302,328]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Holotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
<specimenCode id="6D6CF13FFFF4AF56A50B6200FD85FE95" box="[315,498,302,328]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">MFLU 21–0291</specimenCode>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D755944FFF4AF56A48D627CF8B1FDB5" blockId="7.[136,1452,266,1696]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A48D627CFD56FEB1" box="[189,289,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Saprobic</emphasis>
on dead leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A5C9627CFF6BFEB6" authority="L. Sexual" authorityName="L. Sexual" box="[505,796,337,364]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Cocos" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nucifera">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A5C9627CFED3FEB1" box="[505,676,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Cocos nucifera</emphasis>
L. 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A6FD627FFF6BFEB6" bold="true" box="[717,796,337,363]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Sexual</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A714627CFF02FEB1" bold="true" box="[804,885,338,364]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">morph</emphasis>
Undetermined. 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A01D627FF892FEB1" bold="true" box="[1069,1253,337,364]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Asexual morph</emphasis>
Hyphomycetous. 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A4B86258FC9BFE4D" box="[136,236,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Colonies</emphasis>
on natural substrate, superficial, in groups, scattered, black, velvety, glistening, with conidia readily liberated when disturbed. 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A57462B4FDC5FE69" authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" box="[324,434,410,436]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A57462B4FDC5FE69" box="[324,434,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Mycelium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
immersed in the substrate, composed of septate, branched, smooth, hyaline to pale brown hyphae. 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A4D96290FDF9FE05" box="[233,398,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Conidiophores</emphasis>
micronematous, mononematous, hyaline, smooth. 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A7E26290F8C0FE05" box="[978,1207,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
9–13 × 11–13 μm (x̅ = 10.5 × 12.0 μm, n = 20), holoblastic, monoblastic, determinate, terminal, globose to subglobose or cup-shaped, integrated, connected at the base of conidia, smooth, guttulate, hyaline. 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A7826128F87BFDFD" box="[946,1036,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Conidia</emphasis>
26–30 × 14–17.5 μm (x̅ = 28 × 15.5 μm, n = 50), acrogenous, solitary, ellipsoidal to obovoid, flattened, muriform, smooth-walled, dark brown to black at apical, pale brown at basal, guttulate, usually with a smooth hyaline conidiogenous cell attached.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D755944FFF4AF56A48D615FFD4FFD25" blockId="7.[136,1452,266,1696]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A48D615FFD83FD56" bold="true" box="[189,500,625,651]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Culture characteristics:—</emphasis>
Conidia germinating on PDA within 12 hr at 25 °C, not sporulating after two months. Surface with hyphal growth, circular, umbonate, fluffy, White at the margin, dark brown to black at the middle; reverse white to pale brown at the margin, black at the middle. 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A6C86194FF1CFD09" authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" box="[760,875,698,724]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">Mycelium</taxonomicName>
superficial, circular, partially immersed, hyaline to brown, smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D755944FFF4AF56A48D602FFE8FFC55" blockId="7.[136,1452,266,1696]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A48D602FFDE8FCC6" bold="true" box="[189,415,769,795]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Material examined</emphasis>
:— 
<materialsCitation id="8DA25319FFF4AF56A5F0602CF9D0FC9C" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3783280302" collectingDate="2020-12-08" collectionCode="MFLU, MFLUCC" collectorName="X. G. Tian" country="Thailand" location="Muang District" municipality="Muang District" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" specimenCode="MFLU 21-0291, MFLUCC 21-0154" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Chiang Rai Province" typeStatus="holotype">
<collectingCountry id="45DD19D4FFF4AF56A5F0602CFE21FCC1" box="[448,598,770,796]" name="Thailand" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">THAILAND</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="FF0E97A6FFF4AF56A650602CFF3DFCC1" box="[608,842,770,796]" country="Thailand" name="Chiang Rai" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Chiang Rai Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingMunicipality id="DD11C33EFFF4AF56A765602CF876FCC1" box="[853,1025,770,796]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Muang District</collectingMunicipality>
, on decaying leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A132602CF9DCFCC1" box="[1282,1451,770,796]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Cocos" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nucifera">
