<paragraph id="3D755944FFF4AF56A48D60BCF831FA81" blockId="7.[136,1452,266,1696]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A48D60BCFD51FC71" bold="true" box="[189,294,914,940]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Notes:—</emphasis>
In the phylogenetic analyses, our new strains of 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A7B360BCF957FC71" authorityName="X. G. Tian &amp; Tibpromma" authorityYear="2022" box="[899,1312,914,940]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangraiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A7B360BCF957FC71" box="[899,1312,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Pseudoberkleasmium chiangraiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 21–0154, MFLUCC 21–0161 and MFLUCC 21–0162) clustered as a sister clade to 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A06E6099F952FC0D" box="[1118,1317,950,976]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangmaiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A06E6099F952FC0D" box="[1118,1317,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">P. chiangmaiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 17–2088, MFLUCC 17–1809 and MFLU 21–0290) with a 76% ML bootstrap support value (
<figureCitation id="A5F145C1FFF4AF56A08260F4F958FC29" box="[1202,1327,986,1012]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1857,1879]" captionTargetBox="[195,1417,543,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-188@4.[151,1436,530,1829]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. RAxML tree based on analyses of combined LSU, SSU, ITS, TEF1-α and RPB2 dataset. The tree is rooted with Lophiostoma crenatum (CBS 629.86) and L. arundinis (CBS 621.86). Bootstrap values for ML ≥ 75% and Bayesian posterior probabilities (PP) ≥ 0.95 are labelled on the nodes. The newly obtained sequences are indicated in red, while type strains are in black/red bold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577521" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577521/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">FIGURE 1</figureCitation>
). Our new isolate 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A4E760D0FE1BFBC5" authorityName="X. G. Tian &amp; Tibpromma" authorityYear="2022" box="[215,620,1022,1048]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangraiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A4E760D0FE1BFBC5" box="[215,620,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Pseudoberkleasmium chiangraiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 21–0154) resembles 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A7EC60D1F8F4FBC5" box="[988,1155,1022,1048]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pandanicola">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A7EC60D1F8F4FBC5" box="[988,1155,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">P. pandanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having micronematous, mononematous conidiophores and muriform, ellipsoidal to obovoid, flattened guttulate conidia. However, our new isolate (MFLUCC 21–0154) differs from 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A6526769FF7DFBBD" box="[610,778,1094,1120]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pandanicola">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A6526769FF7DFBBD" box="[610,778,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">P. pandanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its conidia that are dark brown to black at the apex and pale brown at the base, while 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A5E06745FE00FB59" box="[464,631,1130,1156]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pandanicola">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A5E06745FE00FB59" box="[464,631,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">P. pandanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has brown to olivaceous green conidia (
<bibRefCitation id="595B24B5FFF4AF56A0046744F94DFB59" author="Tibpromma, S. &amp; Hyde, K. D. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Bhat, D. J. &amp; Phillips, A. J. L. &amp; Wanasinghe, D. N. &amp; Samarakoon, M. C. &amp; Jayawardena, R. S. &amp; Dissanayake, A. J. &amp; Tennakoon, D. S. &amp; Doilom, M. &amp; Phookamsak, R. &amp; Tang, A. M. C. &amp; Xu, J. &amp; Mortimer, P. E. &amp; Promputtha, I. &amp; Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N. &amp; Khan, S. &amp; Karunarathna, S. C." box="[1076,1338,1130,1156]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref8123" refString="Tibpromma, S., Hyde, K. D., McKenzie, E. H. C., Bhat, D. J., Phillips, A. J. L., Wanasinghe, D. N., Samarakoon, M. C., Jayawardena, R. S., Dissanayake, A. J., Tennakoon, D. S., Doilom, M., Phookamsak, R., Tang, A. M. C., Xu, J., Mortimer, P. E., Promputtha, I., Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N., Khan, S. &amp; Karunarathna, S. C. (2018) Fungal diversity notes 840 - 928: micro-fungi associated with Pandanaceae. Fungal Diversity 93: 1 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 018 - 0408 - 6" type="journal article" year="2018">
Tibpromma 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A08F6745F880FB59" box="[1215,1271,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Our new isolate 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A4EA67A0FE07FB75" authorityName="X. G. Tian &amp; Tibpromma" authorityYear="2022" box="[218,624,1166,1192]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangraiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A4EA67A0FE07FB75" box="[218,624,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Pseudoberkleasmium chiangraiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 21–0154) morphologically differs from 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A0F267A1F9F0FB75" box="[1218,1415,1166,1192]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangmaiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A0F267A1F9F0FB75" box="[1218,1415,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">P. chiangmaiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the colour of conidia (dark brown to black at apical, pale brown at basal vs. yellow to brown) and smaller size (25.5– 30.0 vs. 30–35 μm) (
<bibRefCitation id="595B24B5FFF4AF56A54067F8FE47FB2D" author="Hyde, K. D. &amp; Tennakoon, D. S. &amp; Jeewon, R. &amp; Bhat, D. J. &amp; Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N. &amp; Rossi, W. &amp; Leonardi, M. &amp; Lee, H. B. &amp; Mun, H. Y. &amp; Houbraken, J. &amp; Nguyen, T. T. T. &amp; Jeon, S. J. &amp; Frisvad, J. C. &amp; Wanasinghe, D. N. &amp; Lucking, R. &amp; Aptroot, A. &amp; Caceres, M. E. S. &amp; Karunarathna, S. C. &amp; Hongsanan, S. &amp; Phookamsak, R. &amp; Silva, N. I. &amp; Thambugala, K. M. &amp; Jayawardena, R. S. &amp; Senanayake, I. C. &amp; Boonmee, S. &amp; Chen, J. &amp; Luo, Z. L. &amp; Phukhamsakda, C. &amp; Pereira, O. L. &amp; Abreu, V. P. &amp; Rosado, A. W. C. &amp; Bart, B. &amp; Randrianjohany, E. &amp; Hofstetter, V. &amp; Gibertoni, T. B. &amp; Soares, A. M. &amp; Plautz, H. L. &amp; Sotao, H. M. P. &amp; Xavier, W. K. S. &amp; Bezerra, J. D. P. &amp; Oliveira, T. G. L. &amp; Souza Motta, C. M. &amp; Magalhaes, O. M. C. &amp; Bundhun, D. &amp; Harishchandra, D. &amp; Manawasinghe, I. S. &amp; Dong, W. &amp; Zhang, S. N. &amp; Bao, D. F. &amp; Samarakoon, M. C. &amp; Pem, D. &amp; Karunarathna, A. &amp; Lin, C. G. &amp; Yang, J. &amp; Perera, R. H. &amp; Kumar, V. &amp; Huang, S. K. &amp; Dayarathne, M. C. &amp; Ekanayaka, A. H. &amp; Jayasiri, S. C. &amp; Xiao, Y. &amp; Konta, S. &amp; Niskanen, T. &amp; Liimatainen, K. &amp; Dai, Y. C. &amp; Ji, X. H. &amp; Tian, X. M. &amp; Mesic, A. &amp; Singh, S. K. &amp; Phutthacharoen, K. &amp; Cai, L. &amp; Sorvongxay, T. &amp; Thiyagaraja, V. &amp; Norphanphoun, C. &amp; Chaiwan, N. &amp; Lu, Y. Z. &amp; Jiang, H. B. &amp; Zhang, J. F. &amp; Abeywickrama, P. D. &amp; Aluthmuhandiram, J. V. S. &amp; Brahmanage, R. S. &amp; Zeng, M. &amp; Chethana, T. &amp; Wei, D. &amp; Reblova, M. &amp; Fournier, J. &amp; Nekvindova, J. &amp; do Nascimento Barbosa, R. &amp; dos Santos, J. E. F. &amp; de Oliveira, N. T. &amp; Li, G. J. &amp; Shang, Q. J. &amp; Phillips, A. J. L. &amp; Kuo, C. H. &amp; Camporesi, E. &amp; Bulgakov, T. S. &amp; Lumyong, S. &amp; Jones, E. B. G. &amp; Chomnunti, P. &amp; Gentekaki, E. &amp; Bungartz, F. &amp; Zeng, X. Y. &amp; Fryar, S. &amp; Tkalcec, Z. &amp; Liang, J. &amp; Li, G. &amp; Wen, T. C. &amp; Singh, P. N. &amp; Gafforov, Y. &amp; Promputtha, I. &amp; Yasanthika, E. &amp; Goonasekara, I. D. &amp; Zhao, R. L. &amp; Zhao, Q. &amp; Kirk, P. M. &amp; Liu, J. K. &amp; Yan, J. &amp; Mortimer, P. E. &amp; Xu, J. &amp; Doilom, M." box="[368,560,1238,1264]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" pagination="1 - 242" refId="ref5779" refString="Hyde, K. D., Tennakoon, D. S., Jeewon, R., Bhat, D. J., Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N., Rossi, W., Leonardi, M., Lee, H. B., Mun, H. Y., Houbraken, J., Nguyen, T. T. T., Jeon, S. J., Frisvad, J. C., Wanasinghe, D. N., Lucking, R., Aptroot, A., Caceres, M. E. S., Karunarathna, S. C., Hongsanan, S., Phookamsak, R., Silva, N. I., Thambugala, K. M., Jayawardena, R. S., Senanayake, I. C., Boonmee, S., Chen, J., Luo, Z. L., Phukhamsakda, C., Pereira, O. L., Abreu, V. P., Rosado, A. W. C., Bart, B., Randrianjohany, E., Hofstetter, V., Gibertoni, T. B., Soares, A. M. d. S., Plautz, H. L., Sotao, H. M. P., Xavier, W. K. S., Bezerra, J. D. P., Oliveira, T. G. L., Souza Motta, C. M., Magalhaes, O. M. C., Bundhun, D., Harishchandra, D., Manawasinghe, I. S., Dong, W., Zhang, S. N., Bao, D. F., Samarakoon, M. C., Pem, D., Karunarathna, A., Lin, C. G., Yang, J., Perera, R. H., Kumar, V., Huang, S. K., Dayarathne, M. C., Ekanayaka, A. H., Jayasiri, S. C., Xiao, Y., Konta, S., Niskanen, T., Liimatainen, K., Dai, Y. C., Ji, X. H., Tian, X. M., Mesic, A., Singh, S. K., Phutthacharoen, K., Cai, L., Sorvongxay, T., Thiyagaraja, V., Norphanphoun, C., Chaiwan, N., Lu, Y. Z., Jiang, H. B., Zhang, J. F., Abeywickrama, P. D., Aluthmuhandiram, J. V. S., Brahmanage, R. S., Zeng, M., Chethana, T., Wei, D., Reblova, M., Fournier, J., Nekvindova, J., do Nascimento Barbosa, R., dos Santos, J. E. F., de Oliveira, N. T., Li, G. J., Ertz, D., Shang, Q. J., Phillips, A. J. L., Kuo, C. H., Camporesi, E., Bulgakov, T. S., Lumyong, S., Jones, E. B. G., Chomnunti, P., Gentekaki, E., Bungartz, F., Zeng, X. Y., Fryar, S., Tkalcec, Z., Liang, J., Li, G., Wen, T. C., Singh, P. N., Gafforov, Y., Promputtha, I., Yasanthika, E., Goonasekara, I. D., Zhao, R. L., Zhao, Q., Kirk, P. M., Liu, J. K., Yan, J., Mortimer, P. E., Xu, J. &amp; Doilom, M. (2019) Fungal diversity notes 1036 - 1150: taxonomic and phylogenetic contributions on genera and species of fungal taxa. Fungal Diversity 96: 1 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 019 - 00429 - 2" type="journal article" year="2019">
Hyde 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A58567F9FD9AFB2D" box="[437,493,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). The nucleotide comparisons revealed that the new strain (MFLUCC 21–0154) is different from 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A57567D5FD9AFAC9" box="[325,493,1274,1300]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pandanicola">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A57567D5FD9AFAC9" box="[325,493,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">P. pandanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(KUMCC 17–0178) in 15/367 bp (4.09%) of the ITS, and 8/848 (0.94%) of the LSU, while, the new strain (MFLUCC 21–0154) is different from 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A7186631FF9CFAE5" box="[808,1003,1310,1336]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangmaiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A7186631FF9CFAE5" box="[808,1003,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">P. chiangmaiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 17–1809 ex-type) in 15/389 bp (3.86%) of the ITS, 6/840 (0.71%) of the LSU, and 49/899 bp (5.45%) of TEF1-α.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D755944FFF4AF56A48D6648FD08F97D" blockId="7.[136,1452,266,1696]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">
Taxa in 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A52A6648FE7DFA5D" authorityName="Tibpromma &amp; K.D.Hyde" authorityYear="2018" box="[282,522,1382,1408]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A52A6648FE7DFA5D" box="[282,522,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Pseudoberkleasmium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have similar morphological characteristics with 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A0036648F8A4FA5D" authorityName="Zobel" authorityYear="1854" box="[1075,1235,1382,1408]" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Berkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A0036648F8A4FA5D" box="[1075,1235,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Berkleasmium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, they are distinct in phylogenetic analyses. 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A5CF66A4FF44FA79" box="[511,819,1418,1444]" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Berkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="nigroapicale">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A5CF66A4FF44FA79" box="[511,819,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Berkleasmium nigroapicale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A75766A5F853FA79" box="[871,1060,1418,1444]" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Berkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sutheppuiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A75766A5F853FA79" box="[871,1060,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">B. sutheppuiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were introduced from 
<collectingRegion id="FF0E97A6FFF4AF56A11066A4F9D0FA79" box="[1312,1447,1418,1444]" country="Thailand" name="Chiang Mai" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Chiang Mai</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="45DD19D4FFF4AF56A4B86680FC99FA15" box="[136,238,1454,1480]" name="Thailand" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, while our new species was collected in 
<collectingRegion id="FF0E97A6FFF4AF56A6F16680FF33FA15" box="[705,836,1454,1480]" country="Thailand" name="Chiang Rai" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Chiang Rai</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="45DD19D4FFF4AF56A7606680FFC3FA15" box="[848,948,1454,1480]" name="Thailand" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Thailand</collectingCountry>
that is geographically not too far. However, 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A4B866FCFDB6FA31" box="[136,449,1490,1516]" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Berkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="nigroapicale">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A4B866FCFDB6FA31" box="[136,449,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Berkleasmium nigroapicale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A5CF66FDFEB7FA31" box="[511,704,1490,1516]" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Berkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sutheppuiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A5CF66FDFEB7FA31" box="[511,704,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">B. sutheppuiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lack molecular data, thus, we compared the morphology of our new species with 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A56166D9FE77F9CD" box="[337,512,1526,1552]" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Berkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="nigroapicale">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A56166D9FE77F9CD" box="[337,512,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">B. nigroapicale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A60866D9FE80F9CD" box="[568,759,1526,1552]" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Berkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sutheppuiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A60866D9FE80F9CD" box="[568,759,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">B. sutheppuiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and found that 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A79B66D9F82EF9CD" box="[939,1113,1526,1552]" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Berkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="nigroapicale">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A79B66D9F82EF9CD" box="[939,1113,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">B. nigroapicale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A0C066D9F9DBF9CD" authorityName="X. G. Tian &amp; Tibpromma" authorityYear="2022" box="[1264,1452,1526,1552]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangraiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A0C066D9F9DBF9CD" box="[1264,1452,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">P. chiangraiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having cylindrical and clavate conidiogenous cells, and broadly clavate conidia (
<bibRefCitation id="595B24B5FFF4AF56A0616534F93DF9E9" author="Bussaban, B. &amp; Lumyong, S. &amp; Lumyong, P. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Hyde, K. D." box="[1105,1354,1562,1588]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" pagination="73 - 85" refId="ref5298" refString="Bussaban, B., Lumyong, S., Lumyong, P., McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Hyde, K. D. (2001) A synopsis of the genus Berkleasmium with two new species and new records of Canalisporium caribense from Zingiberaceae in Thailand. Fungal Diversity 8: 73 - 85." type="journal article" year="2001">
Bussaban 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A0F86535F973F9E9" box="[1224,1284,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
). While, 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A4B86511FD3EF985" box="[136,329,1598,1624]" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Berkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sutheppuiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A4B86511FD3EF985" box="[136,329,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">B. sutheppuiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from our new species in having cylindrical conidiogenous cells with subglobose and very dark brown conidia (
<bibRefCitation id="595B24B5FFF4AF56A548654CFE18F9A1" author="Bussaban, B. &amp; Lumyong, S. &amp; Lumyong, P. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Hyde, K. D." box="[376,623,1634,1660]" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" pagination="73 - 85" refId="ref5298" refString="Bussaban, B., Lumyong, S., Lumyong, P., McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Hyde, K. D. (2001) A synopsis of the genus Berkleasmium with two new species and new records of Canalisporium caribense from Zingiberaceae in Thailand. Fungal Diversity 8: 73 - 85." type="journal article" year="2001">
Bussaban 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A5DF654DFE5EF9A1" box="[495,553,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, we identified the three new isolates as a distinct new species of 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF4AF56A4B865A8FD0FF97D" authorityName="Tibpromma &amp; K.D.Hyde" authorityYear="2018" box="[136,376,1670,1696]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF4AF56A4B865A8FD0FF97D" box="[136,376,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="239">Pseudoberkleasmium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
